PROGRAM SUMMARY Program Title: TRIQS Project homepage: http://ipht.cea.fr/triqs Catalogue identier: { Journal Reference: { Operating system: Unix, Linux, OSX Programming language: C++/Python Computers: any architecture with suitable compilers including PCs and clusters RAM: Highly problem-dependent Distribution format: GitHub, downloadable as zip Licensing provisions: GNU General Public License (GPLv3) Classication: 4.4, 4.6, 4.8, 4.12, 5, 6.2, 6.5, 7.3, 7.7, 20 PACS: 71.10.-w,71.27.+a,71.10.Fd,71.30.+h Corresponding author.
Full documentation of the project is available online: http://ipht.cea.fr/triqs .

Let us mention a state-of-the-art implementation of the hybridisation-expansion quantum impurity solver cthyb (http://ipht.cea.fr/triqs/ applications/cthyb/ ) and the dft tools project which provides an interface be- tween DMFT and DFT packages such as wien2k for realistic computations for strongly- correlated materials ( http://ipht.cea.fr/triqs/applications/dft_tools/ ).
However, they are distributed along with the TRIQS library under GPL license and are available for download on GitHub (https://github.com/triqs ).
The description is neither meant to be complete nor ex- haustive; the online reference documentation ( http://ipht.cea.fr/triqs ) will ll the gaps.
HDF5 (C++ and Python) HDF5 is a standard, portable and compact le format, see http://www.hdfgroup.
Obtaining TRIQS The TRIQS source code is available publicly and can be obtained by cloning the repository on the GitHub website https://github.com/TRIQS/triqs .

Assuming that all dependencies have been installed (refer to the online documentation), the library is simply installed by issuing the following commands at the shell prompt: $ git clone https://github.com/TRIQS/triqs.git src $ mkdir build_triqs && cd build_triqs $ cmake ../src $ make $ make test $ make install By default, the installation directory INSTALL_DIR will be located inside the build di- rectory.

The CT-INT application, for example, is installed as follows: $ git clone https://github.com/TRIQS/ctint_tutorial.git src_ctint $ mkdir build_ctint && cd build_ctint $ cmake -DTRIQS_PATH=INSTALL_DIR_ABSOLUTE_PATH ../src_ctint $ make $ make test $ make install where INSTALL_DIR_ABSOLUTE_PATH is the (absolute) path to the TRIQS installation directory.
The C++examples of this paper, various IPython notebooks and the hello_world are provided in a dedicated GitHub repository https://github.com/TRIQS/tutorials.
Issues should be reported exclusively via the GitHub web site at https://github.com/TRIQS/ triqs/issues .
They are available at https://github.com/TRIQS and will be described in other publications.
